main event: On June 8, 1968, a series of unidentified objects were photographed in Flushing, Queens, New York, by a civilian observer who was unaware of them at the time.
interesting points: The observer reported no visual confirmation of the objects until after the photographs were developed., The objects were described as oval or disc-shaped and luminously yellowish-white., The observer did not initially realize he captured the objects while taking pictures of a sunset., The original negatives were sent to Wright-Patterson Air Force Base for analysis and their integrity was assured by the Air Force., The conclusion of the report stated 'insufficient data' as the investigation of the objects continued.
witness description: a civilian photographer unaware of the objects until reviewing photos of the sunset
